quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,52,"And most surely, We have given them a Scripture which We have detailed with knowledge—guidance and mercy for people who believe."
  7,53,"Are they waiting for anything but its fulfillment? The day its fulfillment comes true, those who forgot it earlier will say, “The messengers of our Lord did come with the truth, so do we have any intercessors to intercede for us? Or could we be returned back to behave differently from the way we behaved before?” They have certainly lost themselves, and whatever they used to fabricate strayed away from them."
  7,54,"Indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord is Allah, the One Who created the heavens and the earth in six days{1}then settled over the Throne. He causes the night to <span class=""h"">overwhelm<sup foot_note=""80071"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>the day, pursuing it persistently, <span class=""h"">for<sup foot_note=""80072"" class=""qiraat"">3</sup> </span>the sun and the moon and the stars are subjected by His command. Truly, His is the creation and the command. Supremely Blessed be Allah, Lord of all realms.",footnotes:1:Six equal intervals of time, which may be six heavenly days, each of them being 1000 earthly years long (see 22:47).
  7,55,"Call upon your Lord in supplication and in secret. Indeed, He does not love the transgressors."
  7,56,"And do not corrupt the earth after its reformation, and call upon Him with fear and ardent hope. Indeed, Allah’s mercy is close to those who excel in doing good."
  7,57,"And it is He Who sends the <span class=""h"">winds<sup foot_note=""80073"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>as <span class=""h"">heralds of glad tidings<sup foot_note=""80074"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>ahead of His mercy until, when they carry up heavy clouds, We{3}drive them to a lifeless land where We send down water, and with it We bring out all kinds of products. Thus We bring out the dead, that you may <span class=""h"">remind yourselves<sup foot_note=""80076"" class=""qiraat"">4</sup> </span>.",footnotes:3:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
